<p><strong>Lusat's Glintstone Staff</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Glintstone Staffs" href="/Glintstone+Staffs" target="">Glintstone Staff</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Lusat's Glintstone Staff</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a>&nbsp;and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Intelligence" href="/Intelligence" target="">Intelligence</a> and is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a> for conjuring high sorcery damage.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Staff of the primeval glintstone sorcerer Lusat. Only those who</em><br><em>have glimpsed what lies beyond the wisdom of stone may wield it.</em></p> 
 <p><em>Enhances power of all sorceries, but consumes additional FP.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Lusat's Glintstone Staff in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Lusat's Glintstone Staff weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Sellia, Town of Sorcery" href="/Sellia,+Town+of+Sorcery">Sellia, Town of Sorcery</a>: Found in a chest north of the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Nox Swordstress &amp; Nox Priest" href="/Nox+Swordstress+&amp;+Nox+Priest" target="">Nox Swordstress &amp; Nox Priest</a>&nbsp;boss duo's chamber after defeating them. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive map?id=3229&amp;lat=-172.628125&amp;lng=147.065158&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+map?id=3229&amp;lat=-172.628125&amp;lng=147.065158&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Elden Ring Map here</a>]</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Lusat's Glintstone Staff Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>:&nbsp;No Skill. This armament has no skill. If the armament in the other hand has a skill, that skill will be used instead.</li> 
 <li>This weapon can be used without meeting the 10 Str requirement - it does not impact the Sorcery Scaling modifier at all and only has an effect on the melee damage of the staff</li> 
 <li>This weapon cannot be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a>&nbsp;nor enchanted with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic" href="/Magic" target="">Magic</a>.</li> 
 <li><strong>Lusat's Glintstone Staff</strong> can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a></li> 
 <li>50% increased FP cost. High sorcery scaling. No increase to sorcery damage outside of innate sorcery scaling. At 80 and 99 INT, the extra scaling grants ~11% more damage over the Carian Regal Scepter.</li> 
 <li>Sorcery scales at 413 with 80 <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Intelligence" href="/Intelligence">INT</a></li> 
 <li>While Lusat's Staff does not provide any specific advantages for his personal school of spells (<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Glintstone Stars" href="/Glintstone+Stars">Glintstone Stars</a>, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Star Shower" href="/Star+Shower">Star Shower</a>, and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Stars of Ruin" href="/Stars+of+Ruin">Stars of Ruin</a>), all of those spells are multi-projectile spells, which, due to the way defenses and absorptions work, will perform better when you maximize damage of individual casts (as opposed to increasing the quantity of spells cast - see <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Azur's Glintstone Staff" href="/Azur's+Glintstone+Staff">Azur's Glintstone Staff</a>).&nbsp; 
  <ul> 
   <li>Wearing <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Lusat's Glintstone Crown" href="/Lusat's+Glintstone+Crown">Lusat's Glintstone Crown</a> will further enhance this small niche of Glintstone sorceries</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;500</li> 
 <li>Other notes and player tips go here</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
